title: Deep Space Dangers
short_desc: After weeks without food, the crew passes through a toll booth and manages to crash the ship again.

content.text: t!8ball Does Emmett wake up from the pilot's seat?
ðŸŽ± | Concentrate and ask again, Zander.
t!8ball Does Sanya finally get her outfit right?
> ðŸŽ± | As I see it, yes, Brakia.
Sanya sighs in relief, having managed to find a pair of shorts that properly fit her body.
Finally...
Some shorts that fit.
t!8ball Does Matieu go to the fridge, only finding all the bread is gone?
ðŸŽ± | It is certain, Enchantingtable2013.
Matieu slams the pantry door closed, irritated.
WHO ATE ALL THE DARNED BREAD?!
Seth rubs his eyes and gets up from his messy bed and last night's hookup. He gets up and heads to the kitchen, making a mental note to airlock the lady sleeping on his bed later.
We used it for dinner last night.
Jim was doing pushups in his room, holding his bionic arm behind him.
Five hundred ninety nine... Six hundred!
Jim picks himself off the ground and flexes his arm. He breathes deeply out of partial exhaustion.
I don't think I even broke a sweat!
As it turns out, Emmett ate the last crumbs of bread. He's peacefully sleeping in the pilot's chair.
t!8ball Does Deyner finish tuning up Chompsky's flamethrower?
ðŸŽ± | Most likely, Deyner.
t!8ball Does Seth airlock a female shapeshifter that Emmett had some alone time with?
ðŸŽ± | Concentrate and ask again, Bagelwrecker.
t!8ball Has Seth airlocked the fridge?
ðŸŽ± | Ask again later, Bagelwrecker.
Iris is ribbon dancing in her room with her stuff pushed out of the way.
Deyner yells in an attempt to get Chomsky's attention, given that he does not have a comms watch yet.
Chomsky!!
Chomsky!! Come to my room!!!!
After overhearing Matieu over the comms, Jim gives an audible, sarcastic sigh.
Why are you guys so scared about losing food, we'll find something eventually.
Seth checks the pantry and notices a sack of potatoes on the floor that have started to rot, the package having been nibbled into.
We could always go raid an asteroid farm.
He stands up and takes out his Desert Eagle, searching about to find any pests lurking on his ship.
t!8ball Is KYL300 discharged?
ðŸŽ± | Ask again later, ProfessorTree.
Jim tries his best to mimic Matieu's voice, rolling his eyes.
Emmett, I dont feel so good... Wah, wah, wah.
Jim's voice becomes gruff.
Nut up, Matieu!
Matieu snaps at his watch, his gizzard growling.
Oh, shut up! Your body's like half robot. You subsist off of nuts and bolts.
After not receiving a response from Chomsky, Deyner puts the finished flamethrower on his workbench.
Eh, time to get working on other stuff...
Deyner takes out an incomplete prototype of his to regulate his icy disposition and starts to tinker with it.
Garrick peeks out of the hallway and into the kitchen, watching Seth patrol around the kitchen and nearby rooms like a soldier.
What?
Yeah, an asteroid farm doesn't sound like a bad idea.
Seth cocks his gun as he notices the couch being misaligned, and crumbs leading into a busted ventilation cover.
If the spacesuits didn't get cut up during that space pirate battle, that is.
Jim looks around his room and groans. Another day stuck in deep space, another day wasted doing nothing.
Well, since we have nothing better to do, I guess I'll start installing the camera systems. Just in case we land.
Jim leaves his room, heading towards a supply closet.
Matieu moans as his gizzard continues to grumble.
Man I could really go for some sourdough right now...
As Iris continues to ribbon dance, the ribbon catches on her leg and she falls with a thump.
She sighs, closing her eyes.
I think that's enough for today...
Iris picks herself up from the floor and puts her ceremonial ribbons on a shelf.
t!8ball Does Jim find the resources needed for a camera system?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, TheBlade.
Deyner feels his stomach as it growls. He sneaks into the kitchen to grab a snack, but ends up finding out that there's no food.
Darn.
He silently walks into his room before being notices by the others, disappointed.
Well, I guess we are out of everything...
Jim shuts the supply closet door.
No food, no equipment... soon we'll run out of feul.
t!8ball Does Garrick come out through the door to regroup with everyone?
ðŸŽ± | Don't count on it, RPretribution.
Garrick smacks his ghostly lips and looks around for the others, given that most of them have left the kitchen.
Where are you guys?
We need to get some Ducketts...
Seth finds the culprit of the hole gnawed into the potato sack. He covers an ear before shooting it point blank with his Desert Eagle.
Don't worry about fuel, I made sure to stock up on fuel at the last fuel station, maybe like 10 space miles back.
Seth grabs the stowaway rodent by its tail.
Jim jumps from the nearby gunshot.
What the hell?! We're under attack!
Yeah, we're under attack... By fucking rodents...
Couldn't you have warned us before shooting in the living room?!
My ship, my rules.
t!8ball Does Emmett wake up and quietly yawn in his position?
ðŸŽ± | Most likely, Zander.
Iris grabs Ignis and walks out of her room. Where to go? She hums softly.
Deyner shuts his door and puts on some protective headgear before laying out the mould for a kusarigama.
Emmett stretches and rubs his eyes. He takes out his wrist and speaks into the ship's comms, his tone unenthusiastic.
Morning, everyone.
This is your pilot, Emmett speaking.
Jim walks around the ship, checking on all the systems.
Deyner takes out a vial and pours it into the mould. He then takes out a hammer and slams it into the mould.
CLANG! CLANG! CLANG!
We're over twenty equinoxes into the depths of the Outer Rim and with little to no food...
Emmett sighs.
Seth drags the rodent over to the kitchen counter.
That's why we have Sanya.
He takes out a knife and starts to skin the poor creature.
Iris sighs and mumbles.
We already know that, Emmett...
Sanya rolls her eyes and interjects into her wrist.
Seth, I'll stab you.
Then we'll see who's food.
Garrick takes out a pillow from his pockets and smothers his face into it, dying of boredom as his fellow crewmates have had to conserve their energy. He speaks into his pillow to Seth, muffled.
Don't eat Sanya.
Emmett realizes his sullen tone and acts a bit more cheery. There's no need to be so down.
However, that doesn't mean we need to get our spirits down.
Sanya stands from her bed and puts on her sword carrier, just in case.
Matieu sits at the table in the kitchen, watching Seth chop up the rodent.
Since when did the plant come back to life?
Jim makes his way to the cockpit, waving down Emmett.
Is there anything in our path to land?
Deyner whips out his phone and sends Emmett a message from it.
"I have at least one days worth of rations if needed :)"
t!choose kitchen | cockpit | pool | lounge
ðŸ¤” | Brakia, I pick pool!
Guess I'll head to the pool.
Sanya takes a deep breath and walks to the pool, her hand cautiously near her Dreadsword.
Emmett eyeballs Jim and gets distracted by his CrabPhone vibrating. He whips out his phone and sends Deyner a message back.
"For twelve people, Deyner?"
t!8ball Does Chomsky abandon Garrick and meet Sanya at the pool?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook good, PlasmaPerson.
Garrick picks his face up from his pillow and watches as Chomsky ditches him.
Well, jeez'. Alrighty then.
Deyner sends another message.
"I don't eat breakfast or lunch Emmett"
Chomsky rolls his eyes as he opens the door to the pool.
We'll talk later, garrick.
Chomsky shuts the door to the pool behind him and comes across Sanya, who is currently just staring at the pool.
Hey, Sanya.
Sanya tilts her head a bit towards Chomsky, her body still facing the pool.
What are you doing here?
Garrick blows a raspberry at Chomsky and floats through the door to the lounge. He sits on their futon and turns on the holovision, bored.
Hey, Emmett, is there any place to land soon?
Chomsky raises an eyebrow, puzzled by Sanya's response.
What? I'm not allowed to use the pool?
Emmett taps on his navigation panel and zooms out, seeing nothing of value.
Not that I know of, Jim.
Sanya relaxes her body, realizing how tense she seems.
It's just strange to see you here...
Deyner opens up his door and screams.
Chomsky!!! Come get your flamethrower!
Chomsky, unable to hear Deyner, leans on the wall and folds his arms.
As opposed to somewhere else on the ship?
Garrick peeks up from the futon, having heard Deyner clearly.
OOH! I WANT IT!
He quickly floats to deyner's room to snag the flamethrower.
Hm...
Sanya's hand is instinctively on her sword handle.
No, Garrick!
Deyner holds Chomsky's flamethrower tightly.
Chomsky puts up his hands and shakes his head, finding it absurd that Sanya is so on edge.
Relax. I'm not going to kill you.
Emmett gets up and stretches. His fur is roughened up and matted from how hungry he's been.
Iris sighs.
Well, Sanya seems to have gone back to the pool, so pool it is, I guess.
Iris turns around and heads back to her room to change into her swimsuit.
Garrick clasps his hands repeatedly, nearing the flamethrower.
Give it to me here, I'll give it to him.
Garrick smirks.
Yeeeaaah...
Seth grows tired of slicing up the rodent and leaves it on the countertop. Instead, he heads to Iris's room and opens the door slightly, peeking in.
He watches as she undresses, smiling to himself.
Emmett speaks over the ship's intercom.
You guys going to the pool?
Deyner sighs and lifts the flamethrower away from Garrick.
Chomsky, I swear to god come get your mother trucking flamethrower or I'll give it to Garrick!
Overhearing Deyner's voice from Garrick's active comms, Chomsky speaks into his wrist.
I don't even have my weapon right now, Garrick.
Jim puts a finger to his mouth and leaves the cockpit in open thought.
Might need to check on the cell to make sure its up... Just in case we manage to run completely out of grass again.
As Iris strips down to her undergarments, she notices that her door was opened. She furrows her brow angrily as she notices Seth entering her room.
Get the hell out, Seth!
Seth rolls his eyes and groans.
No fun.
Jim chuckles to himself and puts his watch to his face.
Don't want that to happen again, do we Emmett?
Huh? I didn't get what you said.
Emmett stands from the pilot's seat and holds his stomach.
Chonk, don't come get your weapon.
Go. Away!
Iris covers her chest.
But I'm at the pool. Have Deyner bring it to me.
He's gonna steal it...
I would never steal it, Deyner.
Garrick holds out his hands for the flamethrower.
Well then, you paragon of virtue. You bring it to me.
Chomsky heads to the pool restroom and changes into some swim trunks. Afterwards, he dips his toe into the gelatin.
The pool's quite heated. Feels a bit off from normal water.
Sanya shrugs and watches as Chomsky slips into the pool.
Guess it was already heated up from last night.
Okay...
Deyner reluctantly gives Garrick the flamethrower.
t!8ball Does Iris shove Seth out of her room and lock the door?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, Jelsafan0.
Iris slams the door and locks it behind him.
Deyner looks around Garrick.
Move Garrick, I need to speak with Chomsky, wherever he is.
Psst... you can just go through me to the pool.
Garrick admires Chomsky's flamethrower.
Emmett weakly walks over to the poolside.
Hey guys...
Emmett coughs.
Seth folds his arms angrily.
Jeez, what a rude woman.
Sanya notices Emmett's disposition and heads over to him.
Hey Emmett.
Deyner, as directed, walks through Garrick and to the pool.
t!8ball Does Matieu also head to the pool area?
ðŸŽ± | Reply hazy try again, Enchantingtable2013.
Iris holds her head back in irritation and changes into her swimsuit quickly before unlocking the door and heading to the pool.
Following Iris, Deyner also makes his way to the pool.
Chomsky? Where are you?
Emmett whines like a puppy.
Sanya, I feel weak, man.
Chomksy flows within the pool, his body lying face up. He softly waves, focusing on keeping himself afloat.
Over here, dude.
Sanya glares at Deyner and Iris entering the pool area.
Why is everyone coming to the pool?
Sanya shakes her head and regains her focus on her best friend.
What's wrong, Emmett?
Its the place to be, Sanya.
Chomsky inhales, enjoying himself. He grabs a pool floaty and sits atop of his, staring up into the void.
Iris scoffs.
I came here to swim, duh.
Deyner heads to the the closest part of the pool side to Chomsky, making sure not to enter the pool.
We've been out of food, you know...
Emmett's stomach growls.
As Jim ensures the brig is ready, he speaks into his watch out of concern.
Wait... Someone check on the grass supply!
Emmett's body twitches after hearing Jim mention grass.
And also, out of the... g-thing...
Thank you, Deyner, you're a lifesaver.
Chomsky stares at Deyner, not bothering to leave the pool.
Seth leans in the doorway to the pool, propping the door with his leg.
We had grass sandwiches last night.
Seth mumbles.
Emmett ate most of it.
Sanya eyeballs Seth as he enters.
I see.
Iris sits on the side of the pool, dipping her feet in.
Deyner blinks, having expected Chomsky to jump out of the pool and grab the flamethrower from Garrick, wherever he is.
No problem...
He looks behind him at Emmett.
Emmett I need to talk to you.
Seth scowls at Emmett.
Hence why we're out of bread...
Emmett furrows his brow at Seth's comments.
Shut up, Seth. I didn't eat shit last night.
He perks up, shifting back to Deyner.
Yes, Deyner?
Can you follow me?
Emmett shrugs.
I mean, I can. But why?
Chomsky feathers his fingers through the aeroslime.
What is this pool made of, Anyway?
Garrick plays around with the flamethrower, pretending to shoot it at various things in Deyner's room, complete with various pew sounds and raspberries being blown.
Where is everyone...?
Not bothering to give Emmett an answer, Deyner walks to the navigation room.
Iris sighs, closing her eyes and relaxing.
Emmett watches as Deyner leaves him in confusion.
Okay?
After a couple of moments, he sighs and follows him into the cockpit.
Fine then...
Garrick pockets Chomsky's flamethrower and looks around the ship for a little bit, eventually ending up at the pool.
Sanya stands behind Iris, peering down at her horns.
Hello, Iris. How are you?
Garrick enters the pool area with the others.
'Sup.
Chomsky snaps at Garrick from his pool seat.
Yo.
It's like a gelatinous liquid of sorts, real relaxing. Forgot what it's called.
Iris beams up at Sanya.
A little tired.
Her smile droops after a moment of silence between them.
A little hungry, a little stressed.
Otherwise, fine. Yourself?
Garrick grabs some sunglasses, puts them on, and tips them in Chomsky's direction.
Yo period.
Seth's stomach rumbles.
Unfortunately not edible though.
Sanya observes Iris and notices her swimsuit. She them looks at her own adornments.
I'm glad I have a proper outfit, but overall, I'm good.
You know, Garrick, you could be looking for ways to get food, considering you don't need any for yourself.
Seth takes out a tablet of sorts, metallic red like the Panty Slingshot. He taps on it a bit, accessing an inventory remotely.
Shit, we're out of cigs and space weed...
From within the kitchen, Matieu glares at Seth judgmentally.
You druggie.
Deyner taps on the navigation console to Emmett's chagrin. He accesses a planet, dragging across the screen to get a better look.
This is Jegon-8. It's a food abundant place that's ran by a warlord.
Deyner looks over to Emmett apathetically.
We can take it if you want.
Without skipping a beat, he goes back to his room and works on his kusarigama.
Emmett scoffs at Deyner's abrupt leave and views the map he's been offerred.
Well, bye then.
Yeah, well, I doubt I already have anything.
Garrick shrugs as he floats over the pool.
I don't need to eat, so I don't keep food on me.
Chomsky kicks some aeroslime at Garrick.
No, I mean use maps and stuff to find a planet with food.
Seth groans.
Space weed isn't considered a drug in the GU, birdbrain.
Iris hums a lullaby her father used to sing her as she sits and kicks her legs, feeling content for the first time in a while.
t!8ball Does Deyner successfully make the weapon?
ðŸŽ± | Concentrate and ask again, Deyner.
Garrick gives Chomsky a puzzled expression.
Where would I find that? We're in the middle of space.
After checking the map, Emmett notices the coordinates of the planet Deyner provided him. He yells across the hall as Deyner's room is fairly nearby.
This is on the other side of the galaxy, Deyner!
Matieu rolls his eyes at Seth's namecalling.
Space weed is a gateway drug, whether legal or not. Had a patient who started smoking bowls a while ago. Guess what?
Guy's overdosed three times on morphine since. The guy is addicted to morphine now.
Deyner pops his head around the corner.
You said we needed food, I presented a answer.
Chomsky speaks into his comms, overhearing Emmett's dialogue.
I dunno. Can't this thing go light speed?
Emmett scowls and drags his wrist to his mouth.
Light speed will kill you all in the pool area.
We can't go at light speed. We're not made of light.
This raid could easily feed us for months, Emmett!
Chomsky softly exhales.
Well hyperspace or something then.
I dunno'.
Garrick activates his comms and excitedly speaks into it.
Did I hear raid?
t!8ball Does Seth leave the others and chill on his bed, looking through magazines?
ðŸŽ± | Without a doubt, Bagelwrecker.
Iris has been ignoring her comms, so Garrick's excitement comes as a shock to her.
Emmett starts to calculate how long it would take to bring the Panty Slingshot to Deyner's destination.
Deyner, I don't think this is viable...
I could direct some of the unnecessary power and reroute it to the engines...
t!8ball Does Emmett see something else of interest on the navigation panel?
ðŸŽ± | My sources say no, TheBlade.
I'm down for a raid. I'd finally get to use my flamethrower for something useful.
Jim enters the cockpit, noticing that there's something in the distance in the windshield. He immediately looks to the radar, not seeing whatever's there.
Is this thing even working?
Jim points at where the blip on the radar should be, diverting Emmett's attention.
Deyner scoffs at Emmett's decision.
Why not? This could feed us for a while and it's run by a corrupt warlord?
Seth puts down his full page view of a naked Chromatin human wrapped in crimson drapes to speak into his watch.
We're not doing a raid on a warlord.
Final answer. Sorry.
Seth shakes his head and gets back into his zone.
Trying to raid a warlord would be suicide.
Iris straightens her back.
Good choice.
t!8ball Does Garrick find a marshmallow in his pockets?
ðŸŽ± | Without a doubt, RPretribution.
t!8ball Rather than seeing something on the panel, does Emmett see a intergalactal toll station?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook good, Zander.
T'would be beneficial to raid the guy.
Deyner blinks.
And we would have a steady stream of food from the grateful villagers on the planet though.
Emmett gasps from Jim's observation.
Something in the front!
Seth's eyes glaze over as he looks over his lewd magazines.
Oh wow.
Anyone want a marshmallow?
Garrick shakes the marshmallow in Sanya's face.
Why the hell isn't it showing on the panel?
Iris raises her hand.
I'd like the marshmallow!
Sanya pushes Iris's hand to the side.
I do!
Emmett speaks over the ship's intercom.
I think it's a deep space station, guys!
Looky there, a toll station...
t!8ball Does Garrick eventually give the marshmallow to Sanya?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, definitely, Brakia.
Wait, Garrick, you just pulled a marshmallow out of your pocket. What other food have you got in there?
Iris asked first.
Garrick throws the marshmallow to Iris.
Iris catches it.
Emmett tunes into the toll stations's frequency.
Thanks.
Iris observes the marshmallow, twisting her wrist.
I appreciate it.
Jim leans on the pilot's chair.
Let's see what they have to say....
Panty Slingshot to Toll Station.... Y-28.
Well, that was quick.
Jim looks over to Emmett and mumbles.
What is the purpose of this toll?
Emmett mutes the mic.
Think this might be a hyperlane from the Outer Rim to the Galactic Union, I hope. Usually hyperlanes want some tribute to use them.
Emmett gives Jim a shrug.
But your guess is as good as mine.
Iris gets a sudden headache after holding the marshmallow.
Ah, did you want this, Sanya?
t!8ball Does Deyner successfully finish his kusarigama?
ðŸŽ± | Without a doubt, Deyner.
Toll Station Y-28 to Panty Slingshot, we hear you loud and clear.
Iris looks up at Sanya, holding the marshmallow up to her.
...Sanya?
Sanya glares at Garrick and grits her teeth.
I asked first, ghost. Iris raised her hand.
Deyner, holding his kusarigama, heads back to the pool.
Sanya, you're our chemist, right? I was thinking on making a mixture of sorts.
t!8ball Does Deyner let Chomsky be the chemist like he is?
ðŸŽ± | You may rely on it, PlasmaPerson.
Chomsky pulls himself from the pool and butts in between Deyner and Sanya.
Whatcha' need, Deyner?
Emmett unmutes the nav mic.
Y-28, is there civilization on the other side of this hyperlane?
Do you have any chemical mixtures that burn for a while?
Chomsky rubs his fingers together, feeling a faint stickiness from being in the aeroslime.
Pretty much everything. Yeah.
But, what do you mean by a while? A long while or a short while?
Iris sighs and just eats the marshmallow because Sanya isn't answering.
Deyner tries to compose himself to mask his intentions, but he does so poorly. He appears to be up to no good.
Can you bring some to my room?
Iris gives a distrustful half-glare to Deyner.
Chomsky raises an eyebrow.
M'kay...
Depends on which lane we choose for your ship to go through.
Chomsky heads to his room and brings a chemical container labeled "t5G" to Deyner's room.
We need the closest civilization to here...
Emmett accesses the crew's bank account and realizes that they're quite broke.
We're out of D's though.
Deyner grabs the chemical container.
Thank you, Chomsky.
Chomsky tilts his head.
What do you need it for?
The operator sounds apathetic to the crew's financial woes.
Well, Slingshot, guess you can't go through then.
Deyner gives a guilty smile.
Nothing...
Emmett sighs and browses to the crew's credit tab. It's looking quite rough.
Take my credit, Y-28.
I'll pay it later.
Garrick looks out the poolside, noticing the toll booth. He speaks into his comms.
Oh, for Dread's sake. Is there any other way we can get around it?
Chomsky nods slowly.
Uh huh... Welp, I'll trust you know what you're doing. See ya'.
Chosmky slowly edges out the room and heads back to the pool.
The operator groans audibly over the mic.
Let me check your tab.
t!8ball Does Iris actually get in the pool?
ðŸŽ± | As I see it, yes, Jelsafan0.
Panty Slingshot, it says here you have over 13,000,000 Ducketts in debt for the tolls.
Jim's eyes cartoonishy bulge out of his head from hearing the amount.
Thirteen... million?!!
Sorry can't let you through until you pay.
Deyner peeks into the kitchen from a hallway and yells.
Iris, can you please come to my room?
Iris stands in the shallow end of the pool, and frowns.
What for?
Emmett is taken aback from the Operator's response. While the VP's GU debt is poor, it's not thirteen million Duckett poor.
Y-28, I think you're mistaken. Are you reading our dues upside down? I've paid every time we've gone through these.
A surprise...
Deyner heads back to his room ominously.
Iris sighs heavily.
Fine.
She gets out of the pool, grabbing a towel and wrapping it around her, following Deyner.
Chomsky casually watches as Iris leaves the pool, tipping his sunglasses to get a better look at her figure.
Man...
He then dips back into the pool from his floaty and holds himself at the top.
Seth turns another page in his lewd magazine and finds an insect-like creature with dozens of legs in a bikini. He huffs in disgust and turns to another page.
Guess me having sex with them wasn't enough to stop them from putting it on my tab.
How have I never been in this pool before?
Chomsky relaxes his body in pure bliss.
Garrick inspects the gelatin, dipping a ghostly finger into it.
How does this pool even work?
Chomsky shrugs.
No clue. I just know it's fun.
The moment Iris enters his room, Deyner hands her a box without looking at her.
Here. This is to say, I'm sorry for the offense I caused when we first met.
Garrick sits on top of the pool, not really understanding how Chomsky was so relaxed in the slime.
The operator drones on, not even bothering to double check their number they provided.
Once you pay, then you can pass.
Iris gives Deyner a puzzled look, arcing her neck back in defense.
Emmett taps his head on the navigation console in frustration.
Otherwise I'm gonna have to ask you to leave
There's like four other ships in the queue behind you.
Hey Garrick?
Yeah?
Jim watches as Emett tries to think of some response to the stalwart operator.
Emmett, I can attempt to get into their system and make them think that we paid...
So you're a ghost. Does that mean you had a past life?
Emmett groans and speaks into the ship's intercom.
Does anyone have thirteen Ducketts on hand? Just thirteen I need. The crew's account is broke-broke.
Open it, Iris.
Seth widens his eyes at a beauty on his magazine and verbally shoos Emmett away.
Check inside your butthole, Emmett.
Garrick looks up and ponders Chomsky's question.
... You know, I have no idea.
Iris hesitantly takes Deyner's box and opens it. Her eyes widen as she sees his kusarigama he worked on earlier.
Is this...?
I saw you like ribbon dancing so I made this for you.
Don't worry Emmett, I got this.
From the comfort of his bedroom, Seth taps into the console from his tablet.
Toll keeper. This is the captain of the Vortox Pummelers speaking.
Was I not speaking to the captain before?
No. He's like a vice captain. I'm the captain captain.
Anyhow, I hear we have some debt we need to cover.
Chomsky smirks at Garrick.
Hmm. No brain, no memories, I guess. No offense.
Emmett groans at Seth's predictable attempt to prostitute himself to let them pass. He turns on the intercom once more.
No one have any spare Ducketts?
Yes. Thirteen million Duckett debt. If you don't pay up, I'll need to call a tow company or arrest you all.
Seth speaks into his wrist, away from his tablet before returning to it.
Master diplomat right here, watch.
Operator, I think your voice sounds cute, so I presume you're also cute.
I might...
Sanya checks her pockets.
Deyner exclaims in his room, as if Emmett could hear him.
I think I saw some on the kitchen counter!
t!8ball Does Seth convince the toll keeper to have sex with him in exchange for free passage?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, Bagelwrecker.
t!8ball Does Jim find some change in his wallet?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, definitely, TheBlade.
Iris picks up the chain and hook and admires it dumbfoundedly.
Did you make this?
Garrick snaps at Chomsky, giving him a short-lived glare.
Hey, I'm not the one that burned his own parents.
You happen to be a woman, correct?
Yes, but I don't see that as relevant.
Well, I am infamous across the galaxy for being a master at pleasuring pretty women, if you catch my drift.
